On its own, I think this name is fine, but I'm now also thinking about it in context of blob. In blob, this is called `ContainerEncryptionScope` which A) doesn't have `Options` and B) specifies `Container`. So, I almost prefer leaving in `FileSystem` and then maybe we wouldn't need `Options` since this one is now specific to a file system which means its more than a string? If we don't have `FileSystem`, we do need `Options` I think.

Maybe this is a bad thing to bring up now though since yesterday we seemed to decide all languages would call it `EncryptionScopeOptions` except Java which went with `FileSystemEncryptionScopeOptions` I think. :)

