I think this is going to fail:

```YAML
{
  ...
  "DummyContrasts": {"Test": "t"}
}
```

The reason is that instead of changing the `1` in the design matrix to match the column name, it's now going to be `"intercept"`, and when you expand the dummy contrasts to proper contrasts, then the `"name"` will be `"intercept"` so we will never pick the contrast name back up. There's also nothing stopping somebody from explicitly creating a contrast named `"intercept"`, so detecting this case will now be harder.

